title._content: Dellingshausenite matusekabel / Chapel of the family Dellinghshausen

description._content: Dellingshausenite matusekabel Käsmu kabeli juures. Käsmu poolsaar kuulus Aaspere mõisa juurde, mida omas baltisaksa aadlipere von Dellingshausen 1798. aastast kuni 1919. aastani, mil mõis riigistati. - - - Chapel of the family Dellinghshausen by the chapel of Käsmu. The Käsmu peninsula belonged to the Aaspere manor, which was owned by the Baltic German noble family von Dellingshausen from 1798 till 1919, when all large landholdings were nationalised and later resold to farmers by the young republic of Estonia. ca 1900 Viitekood / Reference code: EAA.1451.1.109.3.9 Kirje andmebaasis FOTIS / Description in the database FOTIS: www.ra.ee/fotis/index.php?type=2&id=9527
